      "writtenOn": "2017-06-29T13:21:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think I overlooked this last time, but there\u0027s no reason to use g now.  There\u0027s nothing downstream that\u0027s expecting to read it out of g, so we\u0027re stomping on the register for no good reason.  It\u0027s an unnecessary constraint on the code generation, and mostly just good to avoid for clarity.\n\nNow that we\u0027re also treating it as a mask, let\u0027s go all the way and do it bitwise?\n\n  U32 mask \u003d 0xffffffff;\n  mask \u003d mask \u0026 (mad(r, c-\u003efDR, c-\u003efR0) \u003e\u003d 0);\n  mask \u003d mask \u0026 (r \u003d\u003d r);\n  unaligned_store((uint32_t*)ctx, mask);\n\n  ...\n\n  const U32 mask \u003d unalgined_load\u003cU32\u003e((const uint32_t*)ctx);\n  r \u003d bit_cast\u003cF\u003e(bit_cast\u003cU32\u003e(r) \u0026 mask);\n  g \u003d bit_cast\u003cF\u003e(bit_cast\u003cU32\u003e(g) \u0026 mask);\n  b \u003d bit_cast\u003cF\u003e(bit_cast\u003cU32\u003e(b) \u0026 mask);\n  a \u003d bit_cast\u003cF\u003e(bit_cast\u003cU32\u003e(a) \u0026 mask);",
      "revId": "c52ae680ead2b1734acdb6f940505ccaea3d32aa",
